Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper proposes a Reinforcement Learning (RL) methodology for power management, which falls under the domain of Artificial Intelligence (AI). 
2. cs.LG - The paper uses function approximation within an adaptive RL framework, which is a common technique in the field of Machine Learning (ML) and falls under the sub-category of Learning (LG). 
3. cs.SY - The paper deals with power management of networked Microgrids (MG) in electric distribution systems, which involves control and optimization of complex systems and falls under the sub-category of Systems and Control (SY). 
4. cs.NE - The paper proposes a privacy-preserving learning model, which involves the use of Neural Networks (NN) and falls under the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (NE). 
5. cs.SE - The paper deals with the optimization of power management in a distributed system, which involves software engineering principles and falls under the sub-category of Software Engineering (SE).
